The article is a statement issued by the Commander-in-Chief of the Armed Forces, celebrating the 70th birthday of the United States Air Force. It acknowledges the brave men and women of the Air Force who have defended the nation with unmatched courage and airpower. The statement also recognizes the centennial anniversary of America's entry into World War I and the beginning of fixed-wing air combat. It pays tribute to the early American aviators who flew dangerous missions during the war and expresses gratitude to the current members of the Air Force for upholding a legacy of service and sacrifice. The statement concludes by saluting the service members, veterans, and military families of the Air Force and expressing the hope that God will bless them and the United States of America.